photometry.remarks: Possible supernova was discovered by S. Maticic at Crni Vrh Observatory on four unfiltered CCD images, taken on 2018 Oct. 18.780 - 19.483UT with the 60-cm f/3.3 Cichocki reflector in the course of the Comet and Asteroid Search Program (PIKA). The object is at R.A. = 22h38m03s.37, Decl. = +09d43'17".1 (equinox J2000), which is 7.5" W and 12" N from the center of the apparent host galaxy, LEDA 1369040.
